#%RAML 1.0
title: My API With Types

description: |
  This RAML illustrates a type properties that includes a question mark in its
  name. The expections here is that the question mark is part of the
  property name if either required is explicitly applied to the
  property or someone uses ??. Otherwise, the question mark indicates an optional
  property.

types:
  profile:
    properties:
      preference?: # not optional, ? as part of the property name
        required: true
      foto?: # optional, ? as part of the property name
        required: false
      description??: # optional, ? as part of the property name
      link?: #optional, , ? not part of the property name
